verbose_text: Under the regulation of ovine beta-lactoglobulin promoter and using genomic DNA of the foreign gene, transgenic sheep expressed high level of SERPINA1 (35 mg/mL) and FIB (5 mg/mL) which both possessing major domains similar to caseins, whereas lower level of FIX (1 mg/mL) which has a major domain distinct with caseins.
